The paper deals with the development of an autonomous pipeline for dual-arm functional regrasping of novel familiar objects, which involves semantic segmentation, object pose estimation, non-rigid mesh registration, grasp sampling, handover pose generation, and in-hand pose refinement. These tasks are all related to robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to improve the system's performance (cs.LG) and its potential application in real-world scenarios (cs.SY).
